addPermittedAccount(address).details: Adds the address to the list of permitted accounts. Only external accounts should be added. Adding a contract address will not be permitted to do transaction.

addReward(uint256).details: Admin can only use this function.  Adds SWAPIFY rewards to the current round.

claimRewards(address,uint256).details: claims rewards during the specified round if there are any to be claimed.

currentReward().details: show the current round reward.  Return uint.

drawWinningNumber().details: Admin draws the 4 winning numbers.  (Random numbers between 0-9). Stores data on chain and starts a new round. Updates the mapping for rounds. Only Admin can execute this function.

getRoundHistory(uint256).details: This function shows round data by round number

getUserRoundData(address,uint256).details: This function calculates rewards & show userdata

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

isPermissible().details: Returns true if the caller is among the list of permitted accounts. Only allowed for external accounts.

mintTickets(address,uint256).details: mints SwapifyTICKET and sends it to the specified address.   This will be used in the DEX contract whenever trades get fulfilled.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removePermittedAccount(address).details: Removes or deactivate the address from the list of permitted accounts.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. > Note: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setNonce(uint256).details: set nonce for randomize ticket generation.

setRewardRatio(uint8).details: Admin can change the reward ratio. This ratio represents how many SWAPAFY required to buy 1 SWAPATICKET

submitTicket(address,uint256).details: user will submit the amount of tickets (SWAPATICKETS) and they must have sufficient amount of tickets in their wallet.  This will then create an entry with 4 random numbers between 0 - 9.  Each ticket user submits grants them one entry with 4 different and random numbers between 0 - 9. User can only submit the amount of tickets that is equivalent to the amount of SWAPATICKETS they have in their wallet.   When user submits ticket(s), SWAPATICKETS get burnt in the process.

ticketsInCurrentRound().details: shows array of tickets that are in current round.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateMatchPoolAllocation(uint8,uint8,ui.details: updates the reward allocation ratio for each pool.  Ratios must add up to 1.   Example:  updateMatchPoolAllocation(0.5, 0.3, 0.15, 0.05)
